# Java Logging Standards

> **Prerequisite**: This rule extends `logging.rule.md`. Apply general logging
> rules first.

## Core Prohibitions

- **NEVER** log L4-L5 data (passwords, tokens, payment info, customer content)
- **NEVER** log system secrets (JWT tokens, access tokens, API keys, private
  keys)
- **NEVER** use `System.out.println()` or `e.printStackTrace()`
- **NEVER** use string concatenation in log statements

## Logging Framework

**MUST** use logging-extension SDK >= 1.1.29:

```xml
<dependency>
    <groupId>us.zoom.async</groupId>
    <artifactId>logging-extension</artifactId>
    <version>1.1.29</version>
</dependency>
```

## Logger Declaration

```java
private static final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(YourClass.class);
private final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(this.getClass());
```

## Placeholder Rules

- **L3 Primitive/String** â†’ `{E}`: `logger.info("userId={E}", id);`
- **Object with L3 fields** â†’ `{#}`: `logger.info("data {#}", obj);`
- **L0-L2 Primitive/String** â†’ `{}`: `logger.info("meetingId={}", mid);`

```java
logger.info("User login: userId={E}, time={}", userId, time);
logger.info("Request data {#}", requestObj);
```

## Debug Logging

**RECOMMENDED** check debug level before logging:

```java
if (logger.isDebugEnabled()) {
    logger.debug("Debug message: {}", message);
}
LogUtil.debug(logger, "Debug message: {}", message);
```

## Exception Handling

**NEVER** use e.printStackTrace() for exception handling, use WebLogger
utilities instead:

```java
logger.error("DB error: {}", WebLogger.printStackTrace(e));
logger.error("Error: {}", WebLogger.printTop20StackTrace(e));
```

## Object Annotations

**Class-Level:**

- `@Sensitizable` - Enable field-level sensitivity control
- `@Sensitizable(mode = PrintMode.inclusive)` - Only log `@IncludeElement`
  fields

**Field-Level:**

- `@HiddenElement` - L4/L5 data (exclude from logs)
- `@SensitiveElement` - L3 data (auto-wrap with {E})
- `@IncludeElement` - Include field (with inclusive mode)

**Collections:**

- List/Array/Set/Map with L3 values:
  `@SensitiveElement(type = CryptoMarker.ENCRYPT)`
- Map with L3 keys+values:
  `@SensitiveElement(type = CryptoMarker.ENCRYPT, using = Transfers.MapKeyCryptoTransfer.class)`

### Example

```java
@Sensitizable
class UserRequest {
    @HiddenElement String password;
    @HiddenElement String driverLicense;
    @SensitiveElement String email;
    @SensitiveElement String userId;
    String meetingId;
    @SensitiveElement(type = CryptoMarker.ENCRYPT) List<String> phoneNumbers;
}

logger.info("Request {#}", userRequest);
```

## Recommended Configuration

Add to `logback.xml`:

```xml
<contextListener class="us.zoom.async.logging.extension.logback.classic.CustomContextListener">
    <logEncryptionModeOnE>compatible</logEncryptionModeOnE>
    <logDesensitizeAllFieldsEnable>true</logDesensitizeAllFieldsEnable>
    <logKeyDesensitizeEnable>true</logKeyDesensitizeEnable>
</contextListener>
```

- `logEncryptionModeOnE=compatible` - Auto-applies {#} for non-primitives;
  @Sensitizable/@HiddenElement require {#}
- `logDesensitizeAllFieldsEnable` - Masks all @SensitiveElement fields
  recursively
- `logKeyDesensitizeEnable` - Auto-applies {E} for map keys
